				<h4><a href="http://whay.me/choral-singing/may-month-of-messiah">May: Month of Messiah</a></h4>				
				<div class="postMeta bullet cat-item-10">
					Posted on 19/04/2012					by <a href="http://whay.me/author/Will">Will Hay</a>
					<span></span>									</div>

				<div class="postBody">
					<p>Famous choral music coming up every Saturday in May to which you can listen or participate in.</p>
<p><strong><a href="http://whay.me/wp-content/uploads/messiah.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-2267" style="margin: 5px;" title="Sing Along Messiah - Chester Cathedral" src="http://whay.me/wp-content/uploads/messiah-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a></strong><strong>5th May: Sing Along Messiah &#8211; Chester Cathedral</strong><br />
270 years after the final notes were added to the score at Chester Cathedral. The friends of the cathedral have organised a sing along Messiah day which will coincide with the annual plant sale.<br />
Directed by Philip Rushforth. Organ by Benjamin Chewter. Rehearsal 2pm, Sing through 5:30pm <a title="Cathedral Box Office" href="http://www.intelligent-tickets.com/index.php?th=ch&amp;pg=selectevent&amp;start=1&amp;sel=3">£10 / person</a></p>
<p><strong>12th May: <a title="NES Singing Day" href="http://nestonecumenicalsingers.org.uk/diary/singing-day/">NES Singing Day<br />
</a></strong>St. Michael’s, Little Neston from 10am-3pm. Bring along a sandwich lunch. The choir will be hosting a <a title="Join the Singing Day event on Facebook" href="https://www.facebook.com/events/247326645366099" target="_blank">singing day</a> where we will be exploring a variety of music as well as socialising and looking at ways we can develop the choir. (£5 / person)<br />
<a href="http://chestercathedralchoir.co.uk/events/concerts-events/diamond-jubilee-concert"><img class="alignright  wp-image-2278" style="margin: 5px;" title="Chester Cathedral Choir - Diamond Jubilee Concert" src="http://whay.me/wp-content/uploads/cccwebbanner-180x300.jpg" alt="" width="144" height="240" /></a><br />
<strong>19th May: Sing Along Messiah &#8211; Neston Parish Church<br />
</strong>Come and sing the Messiah at Neston Parish Church on Saturday 19th May at 2pm. Conductor: Will Hay, Organ: Graham Eccles, Tenor: Chris Sennet, Trumpet: Mark Powell.</p>
<p><strong>26th May: <a title="Diamond Jubilee Concert - Chester Cathedral Choir" href="http://chestercathedralchoir.co.uk/?p=985">Chester Cathedral Choir &#8211; Jubilee Concert<br />
</a></strong>&#8216;A Diamond Jubilee Concert&#8217; - Music to include: Zadok the priest, I was glad, My heart is inditing; Crown Imperial, and Blest pair of Sirens. <a title="Cathedral Box Office" href="http://www.intelligent-tickets.com/index.php?th=ch&amp;pg=selectevent&amp;start=1&amp;sel=2">Tickets: £12.50/7.50<br />
</a></p>
<div class="snap_nopreview sharing robots-nocontent"><ul><li class="sharing_label">Share this:</li><li class="share-facebook share-regular"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-facebook share-icon no-text" href="http://whay.me/choral-singing/may-month-of-messiah?share=facebook" title="Share on Facebook"></a></li><li class="share-twitter share-regular"><div class="twitter_button"><iframe allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets/tweet_button.html?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwhay.me%2Fchoral-singing%2Fmay-month-of-messiah&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwhay.me%2Fchoral-singing%2Fmay-month-of-messiah&amp;count=horizontal&amp;text=May%3A%20Month%20of%20Messiah: " style="width:97px; height:20px;"></iframe></div></li><li class="share-google-plus-1 share-regular"><div class="googleplus1_button"><div class="g-plusone" data-size="medium" data-callback="sharing_plusone" data-href="http://whay.me/choral-singing/may-month-of-messiah"></div></div></li><li class="share-email share-regular"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-email share-icon no-text" href="http://whay.me/choral-singing/may-month-of-messiah?share=email" title="Click to email this to a friend"></a></li><li class="share-end"></li></ul><div class="sharing-clear"></div></div>				</div>
				<div class="clear"></div>
