						<div class="single">
				<h4><a href="http://whay.me/piano-teaching/e-newsletter/national-learn-to-play-day">National Learn to Play Day</a></h4>				
				<div class="postMeta bullet cat-item-90">
					Posted on 01/03/2012					by <a href="http://whay.me/author/Will">Will Hay</a>
					<span></span>									</div>

				<div class="postBody">
					<p><a href="http://learntoplayday.com"><img class="alignright  wp-image-2215" style="margin: 5px;" title="Learn to Play Day" src="http://whay.me/wp-content/uploads/2c9d999b0e42165be641ba80e45decf5.jpg" alt="" width="216" height="216" /></a>When planning the forthcoming &#8220;<a title="&quot;Playing Together&quot; concert series" href="http://whay.me/tag/piano-concert/">Playing Together</a>&#8221; concert at All Saint&#8217;s Church in Chester, I hadn&#8217;t quite realised the significance of the date, 31st March, 2012. However it seems like an excellent opportunity to encourage <strong>anyone</strong> to come along to <a title="Playing Together - 31st March 2012" href="http://whay.me/diary/playing-together-31st-march-2012">the concert</a>, be inspired by some musical performances and then head down to their nearest <a title="Dawsons &quot;Learn to Play&quot; Day" href="http://www.dawsons.co.uk/blog/learn-to-play-day-try-a-free-music-lesson">Dawsons store</a> to try a free &#8220;taster&#8221; lesson on an instrument!</p>
<p>National Learn to Play Day has been organised by <a title="Music for all" href="http://www.musicforall.org.uk/">Music for All</a>, the charity of the national musical instrument industry in partnership with the <a title="Musicians Union" href="http://www.musiciansunion.org.uk/">Musicians&#8217; Union</a>, Arts Council England&#8217;s<a title="Take it Away" href="http://takeitaway.org.uk/"> &#8220;Take it Away&#8221; scheme</a>, <a title="Music Teachers .co.uk" href="http://www.musicteachers.co.uk/">musicteachers.co.uk</a> and <a title="MusicRadar" href="http://www.musicradar.com">Musicradar.com</a></p>
<p>&#8220;Playing Together&#8221;<br />
Playing the piano can be a somewhat solitary experience which is why for a year now, I have been actively encouraging my piano/keyboard students to engage with other musicians at the piano, playing duets and trios and with other instruments in small ensembles. <span style="text-align: left;">Students are also encouraged to take part in <a title="Composition Projects" href="http://whay.me/?s=composition+project">composition projects</a> on my </span><a style="text-align: left;" title="Will Hay Piano Tuition : Noteflight Classroom" href="http://nf.whay.me">Noteflight Classroom</a><span style="text-align: left;"> which can result in performance in tandem with music technology!</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://nf.whay.me"><img class="wp-image-2220 aligncenter" style="margin: 5px;" title="In Tandem with Technology" src="http://whay.me/wp-content/uploads/Ruth-composition.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="280" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="snap_nopreview sharing robots-nocontent"><ul><li class="sharing_label">Share this:</li><li class="share-facebook share-regular"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-facebook share-icon no-text" href="http://whay.me/piano-teaching/e-newsletter/national-learn-to-play-day?share=facebook" title="Share on Facebook"></a></li><li class="share-twitter share-regular"><div class="twitter_button"><iframe allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" src="http://platform.twitter.com/widgets/tweet_button.html?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwhay.me%2Fpiano-teaching%2Fe-newsletter%2Fnational-learn-to-play-day&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwhay.me%2Fpiano-teaching%2Fe-newsletter%2Fnational-learn-to-play-day&amp;count=horizontal&amp;text=National%20Learn%20to%20Play%20Day: " style="width:97px; height:20px;"></iframe></div></li><li class="share-google-plus-1 share-regular"><div class="googleplus1_button"><div class="g-plusone" data-size="medium" data-callback="sharing_plusone" data-href="http://whay.me/piano-teaching/e-newsletter/national-learn-to-play-day"></div></div></li><li class="share-email share-regular"><a rel="nofollow" class="share-email share-icon no-text" href="http://whay.me/piano-teaching/e-newsletter/national-learn-to-play-day?share=email" title="Click to email this to a friend"></a></li><li class="share-end"></li></ul><div class="sharing-clear"></div></div>				</div>
